latestIgtvVideos.title: Tie Dye ~ Jhanvi Bhatia
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
“Upcycling turns things into other things which is basically magic”

#page18 & #page19 presents our muse, @jhanviibhatiaa , showing how one can use vegetables to tie dye. 💗 The most fun part of it being that you don’t the final product unless the entire process is over. This is naturally one of the easiest ways for following sustainability. She doesn’t believe in forcing sustainability completely unto others but small steps would matter. ✨

The last part of the video was also a much requested thing, we suggest you to not skip and enjoy & have a good laugh :) #tiedye #naturaltiedye #onionskindye #sustainablefashion #whitetshirt #embroidery #whatisthisbehaviorpooja #biggboss #fashion #styling #design #jhanvibhatia #jsk #bemymuse #bemymusemagazine #emagazine #digitalmagazine

latestIgtvVideos.title: Maa Ka Pyaar Act ~ Jaikishan Bhatia
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
In this video, he plays an out station guy who comes to Mumbai for studies. He is very excited about finally being independent, but later realizes how he misses the small things about being at home & most importantly his mother's love for him, which he used to nag about earlier. Share your views in the comments section 🥰

#page16 & #page17 shows our muse, @jaikishanbhatia_ , presenting an act on mother’s love. That being so important he believes, that it is above all the kinds of love. And we totally agree. 💗

He’s also a tech-savvy person and his tips on sustainable uses of electronics and how to maintain battery health should be covered in the magazine. Last few days left, stay tuned for the launch! ✨

latestIgtvVideos.caption:

#page14 & #page15 of our e-magazine presents our beautiful MUA and her work. 
Don’t you always want to even that foundation? Or would want to take care of the skin while enjoy make up? This video just explains everything you need to know. Not just this, but she’ll also send in some beautiful tips as to how to work it well in the magazine. Stay tuned for the launch ✨

latestIgtvVideos.title: Louis Vuitton Photo Analysis
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Illustrating is so therapeutic, frustrating and just beautiful at the same time.

Back at it after a long time. Illustrated this from the Louis Vuitton @louisvuitton Collection photographed for the @voguemagazine @vogueindia 
This is a photo analysis where you basically sketch and colour the same thing clicked so as to see whether you give correct shades to your colours, give appropriate folds, get the right texture and print/patterns of the fabric and just being able to understand the attire really well. I chose this one since it had all these elements merged together into one beautiful piece. The tartan plaid, formal checks, leather, sequins, metal, everything!! That kinda challenges me to try new things and learn from the mistakes. 
There are quite a few slight changes and don’t even get started with the face structure, awful I know, but this is the best I did deliver. Well, I’m working on faces, sorry about that.

Overall, what’s your feedback?
@lahotyshivangi
